chargeHist.descr: Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent

result.execSummary:
The defendant Charles S Kelley Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: If imposed, the defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program. If revoked, 37 days credit granted. STAYED for probation.

miscConds.notes: Restitution for Burger King is to be paid, as a condition of probation, before any other costs or fees.
Court costs waived. DNA Surcharge to be paid as a condition of probation.

Submit to an AODA assessment, follow through with any treatment, counseling.  No use or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia. Comply with random urine screens.  Maintain absolute sobriety. No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription. Valid prescriptions only with prior agent approval and to be taken only in the manner they are prescribed. No use or possession of any CBD/vaping products.

Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent.
Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent.
No contact with: Victim A or the Burger King listed in the criminal complaint.
Take Thinking for a Change Course.
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.

timeConds.notes: The first 3 months are to be served with Huber, forthwith, with non-working hours and standard release conditions. The remaining 3 months are STAYED, to be used at the agent's discretion. Huber privileges are also at the agent's discretion.
